properties.headline: Wind Chill Advisory issued January 15 at 2:44PM CST until January 16 at 9:00AM CST by NWS Sioux Falls SD
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Wind Chill Advisory, very cold wind chills
expected. Wind chills 25 to 30 below zero. For the Winter Storm
Watch, snow and strong winds with freezing drizzle possible.
Total snow accumulations of 3 to 5 inches and ice accumulations
of a light glaze possible. Winds could gust as high as 45 mph.

* WHERE...Portions of east central South Dakota and northwest
Iowa.

* WHEN...For the Wind Chill Advisory, from 9 PM this evening to
9 AM CST Thursday. For the Winter Storm Watch, from Friday
morning through Saturday afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult. Areas of blowing snow
could significantly reduce visibility. The cold wind chills
could cause frostbite on exposed skin in as little as 30
minutes.
properties.instruction:
Use caution while traveling outside. Wear appropriate clothing, a
hat, and gloves.

Monitor the latest forecasts for updates on this situation.
